i just follow https://google.github.io/styleguide/cppguide.html#Names_and_Order_of_Includes

when i was in google3 i got sick of doing this manually and actually have a python script to do it. (at that time the lint tool would complain, but wouldn't fix it/tell you the fix. not sure if they've improved that since.)

like you say, it usually doesn't matter, but your new friend <libgen.h> is actually a pathological example: everything in that header file is also in <string.h> --- except that they're different functions (that behave differently) with the same names. so having SOP be "implementation header first" keeps us out of mischief when people do stupid things like that.

*hopefully* no-one's doing that to new headers, but like they say in google3, "hope is not a strategy".

if you're really keen on reordering, i'll mail you my script...

